<p><b>JISC</b> (formerly the <b>Joint Information Systems Committee</b>) is a <a href="United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a> <a href="Non-departmental_public_body" title="Non-departmental public body">non-departmental public body</a> whose role is to support post-16 and <a href="Higher_education" title="Higher education">higher education</a>, and <a href="Research" title="Research">research</a>, by providing leadership in the use of ICT (<a href="Information_and_Communications_Technology" title="Information and Communications Technology" class="mw-redirect">Information and Communications Technology</a>) in learning, teaching, research and administration. It is funded by all the UK post-16 and higher education <a href="UK_Research_Councils" title="UK Research Councils">funding councils</a>.</p>
